---
import Feature from '../../layouts/Feature.astro';
---

<Feature
  title="DAEMON MODE"
  subtitle="Pane server lives in its own process. Persistence and remote shells are landing on top."
>
  <div class="roadmap-banner">
    <strong>Daemon process and IPC ship today; persistence and remote domains are still landing.</strong>
    <p>Auto-start, retry, and embedded fallback work now. Crash recovery, multi-client connect, scrollback archive, and SSH / WSL domains are roadmap items. See the <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '')}/roadmap`}>roadmap</a> for current status.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Process Model</h2>
  <p>The pane server (<code>oriterm_mux</code>) runs as a standalone daemon by default and the GUI connects over a Unix domain socket (Linux/macOS) or named pipe (Windows). On first launch the GUI auto-spawns the daemon with a 3-attempt retry; if the daemon cannot be reached, it falls back to embedded mode (single process, no IPC).</p>
  <p>Set <code>process_model = "embedded"</code> in <code>config.toml</code> to skip the daemon entirely — useful in sandboxes and tests.</p>

  <h2>Planned: Sessions Persist</h2>
  <p>The next milestone separates shell session state from window lifetime. Closing the window will leave shells running; reopening will restore scrollback, working directories, and pane layout. Auto-save and crash recovery come with this milestone.</p>

  <h2>Planned: Remote Domains</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>SSH</strong> — open remote shells via SSH with agent forwarding and keepalive, mixed with local panes</li>
    <li><strong>WSL</strong> — Windows Subsystem for Linux integration with auto-detection</li>
  </ul>
</Feature>

<style>
  .roadmap-banner {
    border: var(--border-weight) solid var(--accent);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 8%, transparent);
    padding: 20px 24px;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }

  .roadmap-banner strong {
    color: var(--accent);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .roadmap-banner p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
</style>
